      {
        "comment_id": "2034232488",
        "repo_full_name": "colinhacks/zod",
        "pr_number": 4074,
        "pr_file": "packages/core/package.json",
        "discussion_id": "2034158202",
        "commented_code": "@@ -0,0 +1,129 @@\n+{\n+  \"name\": \"@zod/core\",\n+  \"version\": \"0.1.0\",",
        "comment_created_at": "2025-04-09T00:48:49+00:00",
        "comment_author": "colinhacks",
        "comment_body": "Yeah they'll be independent. My thinking:\r\n\r\n- there will be some additional libraries that rely on `@zod/core` (e.g. `@zod/json`, `@zod/codec`). so there will likely be changes to `zod`, etc that don't require bumps to `@zod/core`, and vice versa.\r\n- this is in the `0.x` version range out of the gate because that's designated for initial development. the plan is to publish v1.0.0 once Zod and Zod Mini are published to `latest`. though I'm slightly tempted just to keep it in `0.x` forever, otherwise it's going to go through major versions very fast...but \r\n- this is published as `latest` because I want to indicate to schema authors that it's stable enough to build against. they can just keep bumping the version as new betas come out (`v0.2`, `v0.3`, etc)\r\n- because Zod Mini will always be pinned to `zod`, I decided to jump it straight to `4.0.0-beta.x`",
        "pr_file_module": null
      }
    ]
  },
